33,"locked":false,"text":"8. Operational Analytics & Financial Reports","version":294,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"bG6","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"8. Operational Analytics & Financial Reports","height":25,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1710239773,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-4702.0119470828358,"angle":0,"y":-13068.533558933059,"width":430.5595703125},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","link":null,"endArrowhead":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"startBinding":null,"index":"bG7","startArrowhead":null,"backgroundColor":"transparent","endBinding":null,"angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1,"version":228,"roundness":{"type":2},"type":"line","updated":1771572857458,"id":"WmLpzC3DL55Sb6snVphZm","x":-4751.0119470828358,"seed":1326995347,"boundElements":[],"y":-12995.533558933059,"opacity":100,"height":1,"points":[[0,0],[728,-1]],"width":728,"frameId":null,"polygon":false,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":1184256435},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#f08c00","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"bG8","backgroundColor":"transparent","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1,"version":189,"roundness":{"type":2},"type":"ellipse","updated":1771591101535,"id":"56TPhIUrWxPpYmBlJ3Drz","x":-4058.0119470828358,"seed":1475210547,"boundElements":[],"y":-13028.533558933059,"opacity":100,"height":24,"width":25,"frameId":null,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":1401206953},{"seed":146788051,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"TyUk7hSlE8hBgrZ1bgQS4","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771591092643,"locked":false,"text":"Fleet Flow","version":162,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"bG9","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Fleet Flow","height":25,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1971c2","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":933533959,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-4726.0119470828358,"angle":0,"y":-13026.533558933059,"width":101.83990478515625},{"seed":1186302931,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"X9-auove9wIuPGdi79-sV","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771579576203,"locked":false,"text":"What it’s for: A quick, \"all-in-one\" screen to see exactly what’s happening with your fleet right now.\n\nThe Big Numbers (KPIs):\n\nActive Fleet: How many vehicles are currently out on the road.\n\nMaintenance Alerts: How many vehicles are stuck in the shop for repairs.\n\nUtilization Rate: A percentage showing how much of your fleet is actually working versus sitting empty.\n\nPending Cargo: How many deliveries are sitting in the warehouse waiting for a driver.\n\nSorting Tools (Filters):\nYou can quickly clean up the view by looking only at specific groups, like:\n\nVehicle Type: Only show trucks, vans.\n\nStatus: Only show vehicles that are \"Ready\" or \"Busy.\"\n","version":29,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"bGH","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"What it’s for: A quick, \"all-in-one\" screen to see exactly what’s happening with your fleet right now.\n\nThe Big Numbers (KPIs):\n\nActive Fleet: How many vehicles are currently out on the road.\n\nMaintenance Alerts: How many vehicles are stuck in the shop for repairs.\n\nUtilization Rate: A percentage showing how much of your fleet is actually working versus sitting empty.\n\nPending Cargo: How many deliveries are sitting in the warehouse waiting for a driver.\n\nSorting Tools (Filters):\nYou can quickly clean up the view by looking only at specific groups, like:\n\nVehicle Type: Only show trucks, vans.\n\nStatus: Only show vehicles that are \"Ready\" or \"Busy.\"\n","height":475,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":406651581,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-3976.1097888905897,"angle":0,"y":-17688.788750980628,"width":1011.9190673828125},{"seed":106600819,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"CwEdAAOOlYTDRtSgR15dX","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771579637863,"locked":false,"text":"What it’s for: This is your digital garage. It’s the place where you add, view, change, or remove every vehicle your company owns.\n\nThe Details You Track:\n\nName\/Model: The specific name\/make of the vehicle.\n\nLicense Plate: The unique ID for each vehicle so you don't mix them up.\n\nMax Load Capacity: How much weight the vehicle can safely carry (in kg or tons).\n\nOdometer: The current mileage on the vehicle’s dashboard.\n","version":57,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"bGI","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"What it’s for: This is your digital garage. It’s the place where you add, view, change, or remove every vehicle your company owns.\n\nThe Details You Track:\n\nName\/Model: The specific name\/make of the vehicle.\n\nLicense Plate: The unique ID for each vehicle so you don't mix them up.\n\nMax Load Capacity: How much weight the vehicle can safely carry (in kg or tons).\n\nOdometer: The current mileage on the vehicle’s dashboard.\n","height":300,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":680226365,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-3985.665491939586,"angle":0,"y":-16950.341251078109,"width":1259.759033203125},{"seed":1431106323,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"k6hiBMq1si-P-yWV7vCVB","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771579713571,"locked":false,"text":"What it’s for: This is the \"brain\" of the operation. It’s where you actually set up deliveries and move goods from one place to another.\n\nHow it Works:\n\nBooking a Trip: You pick a vehicle and a driver that are currently free and ready to go.\nYou enter how much the cargo weighs. If you try to put a 2,000kg load into a 1,000kg van, the system will block you and say, \"Too heavy!\"\n\nTrip Progress: You can track the status of the job as it moves through four stages:\n","version":53,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"bGJ","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"What it’s for: This is the \"brain\" of the operation. It’s where you actually set up deliveries and move goods from one place to another.\n\nHow it Works:\n\nBooking a Trip: You pick a vehicle and a driver that are currently free and ready to go.\nYou enter how much the cargo weighs. If you try to put a 2,000kg load into a 1,000kg van, the system will block you and say, \"Too heavy!\"\n\nTrip Progress: You can track the status of the job as it moves through four stages:\n","height":225,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1797156157,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-3960.1892601058771,"angle":0,"y":-16070.253242277227,"width":1369.138916015625},{"seed":1946359987,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"2mK-3koR_2r345OFIAt9I","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771579763035,"locked":false,"text":"What it’s for: This is where you keep your vehicles healthy. It tracks every time a vehicle goes in for a check-up or a repair.\n\nHow it Works:\n\nLogging a Repair: When a vehicle needs work (like an oil change or new tires), you create a log entry here.\n\nThe \"Auto-Hide\" Rule: As soon as you add a vehicle to a maintenance log, the system automatically marks it as \"In Shop.\"\nThe Benefit: While a vehicle is \"In Shop,\" the Dispatcher cannot see it or pick it for a new trip. \nThis prevents you from accidentally sending a broken truck out on a delivery.","version":12,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"bGK","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"What it’s for: This is where you keep your vehicles healthy. It tracks every time a vehicle goes in for a check-up or a repair.\n\nHow it Works:\n\nLogging a Repair: When a vehicle needs work (like an oil change or new tires), you create a log entry here.\n\nThe \"Auto-Hide\" Rule: As soon as you add a vehicle to a maintenance log, the system automatically marks it as \"In Shop.\"\nThe Benefit: While a vehicle is \"In Shop,\" the Dispatcher cannot see it or pick it for a new trip. \nThis prevents you from accidentally sending a broken truck out on a delivery.","height":225,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":880157661,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-4011.1417237732967,"angle":0,"y":-15343.022624478606,"width":1215.5791015625},{"seed":1344506451,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"kWbic7ewGYi-SoQmwLGKf","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771572857459,"locked":false,"text":"What it’s for: This is the digital \"wallet\" for your fleet. It tracks exactly how much money is being spent to keep your vehicles moving.\n\nHow it Works:\n\nFuel Tracking: Every time a driver fills up the tank, you record how many liters they bought and how much it cost.\n\nCost per Vehicle: The system automatically connects these receipts to the specific vehicle used.\n\nThe Math: It adds up the fuel costs and the repair bills to show you the \"Total Cost\" for each vehicle. This helps you see if a specific truck is becoming too expensive to keep.","version":7,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"bGL","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"What it’s for: This is the digital \"wallet\" for your fleet. It tracks exactly how much money is being spent to keep your vehicles moving.\n\nHow it Works:\n\nFuel Tracking: Every time a driver fills up the tank, you record how many liters they bought and how much it cost.\n\nCost per Vehicle: The system automatically connects these receipts to the specific vehicle used.\n\nThe Math: It adds up the fuel costs and the repair bills to show you the \"Total Cost\" for each vehicle. This helps you see if a specific truck is becoming too expensive to keep.","height":225,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":453725299,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-4004.1936605459214,"angle":0,"y":-14537.047290103063,"width":1738.17822265625},{"seed":1585760243,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"yeDZcgLNcCuJOL1sqDIrZ","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771572857459,"locked":false,"text":"What it’s for: This page is all about the people driving your vehicles. It helps you make sure they are legal to drive and doing a good job.\n\nHow it Works:\n\nThe \"Paperwork\" Check: You store the driver’s license number and when it expires.\n\nThe \"Safety Lock\" Rule: If a driver’s license expires, the system automatically locks them. You won't be able to assign them to any new trips until they renew it.\n\nPerformance Scores: The system gives drivers a \"Safety Score\" based on things like finishing trips on time and whether they've been involved in any accidents or reported issues.\n\nDuty Status: A simple switch to show if a driver is currently \"On Duty,\" \"Taking a Break,\" or \"Suspended.\"","version":7,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"bGM","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"What it’s for: This page is all about the people driving your vehicles. It helps you make sure they are legal to drive and doing a good job.\n\nHow it Works:\n\nThe \"Paperwork\" Check: You store the driver’s license number and when it expires.\n\nThe \"Safety Lock\" Rule: If a driver’s license expires, the system automatically locks them. You won't be able to assign them to any new trips until they renew it.\n\nPerformance Scores: The system gives drivers a \"Safety Score\" based on things like finishing trips on time and whether they've been involved in any accidents or reported issues.\n\nDuty Status: A simple switch to show if a driver is currently \"On Duty,\" \"Taking a Break,\" or \"Suspended.\"","height":275,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":393168403,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-3994.9295762427537,"angle":0,"y":-13719.491850348561,"width":1736.0784912109375},{"seed":892162451,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"9MC9P-OYGAVAL5TUHHEgK","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1771572857459,"locked":false,"text":"What it’s for: This is the \"big picture\" page. It turns all your data into easy-to-read charts and reports so you can make smarter business decisions.\n\nWhat You’ll See:\n\nFuel Efficiency: It tells you which vehicles are \"gas guzzlers\" and which ones are saving you money by calculating how far they go on every liter of fuel.\n\nVehicle Value (ROI): It calculates if a vehicle is actually making you money. It compares the revenue the vehicle brings in against what you spend on its fuel and repairs.\n\nDead Stock Alerts: It highlights vehicles that are just sitting idle and not being used, so you can decide if you should sell them or assign them more work.\n\nOne-Click Reports: You can quickly download a PDF or Excel sheet for monthly meetings, payroll, or tax season.","version":7,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"bGN","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"What it’s for: This is the \"big picture\" page. It turns all your data into easy-to-read charts and reports so you can make smarter business decisions.\n\nWhat You’ll See:\n\nFuel Efficiency: It tells you which vehicles are \"gas guzzlers\" and which ones are saving you money by calculating how far they go on every liter of fuel.\n\nVehicle Value (ROI): It calculates if a vehicle is actually making you money. It compares the revenue the vehicle brings in against what you spend on its fuel and repairs.\n\nDead Stock Alerts: It highlights vehicles that are just sitting idle and not being used, so you can decide if you should sell them or assign them more work.\n\nOne-Click Reports: You can quickly download a PDF or Excel sheet for monthly meetings, payroll, or tax season.","height":275,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":73599923,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-3925.4489439690005,"angle":0,"y":-12874.144157684559,"width":1642.918701171875},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","link":null,"endArrowhead":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"startBinding":null,"index":"bGt","startArrowhead":null,"backgroundColor":"transparent","endBinding":null,"angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":2,"version":110,"roundness":{"type":2},"type":"line","updated":1771572953656,"id":"JWDJoFZGSk-WAxzG1GMTJ","x":-4766.8772755552291,"seed":1510051709,"boundElements":[],"y":-17743.867485031064,"opacity":100,"height":2.857142857144936,"points":[[0,0],[728.57142857142844,2.857142857144936]],"width":728.57142857142844,"frameId":null,"polygon":false,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":1172210973},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"bH5","backgroundColor":"transparent","angle":0,"fillStyle"